            <div type="history" n="locations">
                <head>Locations</head>
                <div type="history" n="locations">
                    <head>Found</head>
                    <p>
                        <rs type="found">found acting as a gate-post at Loughboreen, between
                            Bennetsbridge and Thomastown <ref type="bibliog" target="#MCM1991"
                                        >(<bibl><author>McManus</author>
                                    <date when="1991">1991</date>, <biblScope type="pp"
                                        >75</biblScope></bibl>)</ref>. </rs>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div type="history" n="locations">
                    <head>Original</head>
                    <p>
                        <rs type="origLocation">GPS coordinates of possible original location <geo>-7.130026, 52.579280</geo></rs>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div type="history" n="locations">
                    <head>Last recorded</head>
                    <p>
                        <rs type="lastLocation">On site at Tullaherin close to the round tower. The
                            present location of this stone may be accessed via the <ref
                                target="http://webgis.archaeology.ie/HistoricEnvironment/?SMRS=KK024-062009-"
                                >National Monuments Service Historic Environment viewer on
                                www.archaeology.ie</ref>. </rs>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="history" n="record">
                <head> History of Recording</head>
                <p>Believed to have been removed from Tullaherin monastic site and used as a gate
                    post on lands of Lar Mahon at Loughboreen for 30 years until re-discovered and recorded by
                    Fionnbarr Moore in 1983 and returned to Tullaherin. </p>
            </div>
